docs.abstract: A case in federal court was set to go to trial next month but a settlement reached on Friday makes the civil rights anthem freely available.
docs.snippet: A case in federal court was set to go to trial next month but a settlement reached on Friday makes the civil rights anthem freely available.
docs.lead_paragraph: The two sides in a legal dispute over whether the song “We Shall Overcome” was subject to copyright protection reached a settlement on Friday that put the civil rights anthem in the public domain, lawyers involved in the case said.

headline.main: ‘We Shall Overcome’ Is Put in Public Domain in a Copyright Settlement

docs.abstract: As the social network’s list of woes grows, its 33-year-old founder, Mark Zuckerberg, will have to prove somehow he is not in way over his head.
docs.snippet: As the social network’s list of woes grows, its 33-year-old founder, Mark Zuckerberg, will have to prove somehow he is not in way over his head.
docs.lead_paragraph: For a business built on growing friendships, Facebook is making an astonishing number of enemies. Revelations that some 50 million of its user profiles were inappropriately harvested add to a list of outcries over the social network’s practices. It has come to the point where Facebook’s founder, Mark Zuckerberg, will have to prove somehow he is not in way over his head.

headline.main: Is It Time for More Adult Supervision at Facebook?
